properties.otherAdvice: A reduced speed limit is in place on Tantangara Rd for safety due to construction work associated with Snowy 2.0.

Vehicles between 15 and 28 tonnes are now able to access the valley with Council permission, under stop/slow conditions.

As the area remains a construction site, safety procedures must be followed.

For vehicles between 15 and 28 tonnes to access the site:

  • Please email the Manager Transport and Public Access, Nicole Hume at nhume@bmcc.nsw.gov.au with at least two working days’ notice to obtain a permit for the heavy vehicle access.
  • A permit will be required to be carried and shown to traffic control on site. Traffic controllers will then coordinate access through the site.

Please note that if the same vehicle needs to access the valley multiple times, only one permit will be required. Vehicles over 15 tonnes that are not scheduled to enter the valley will be turned back to ensure safety is maintained on site.

Special event clearways will be in place continuously from 2am Sat 21 Sep to 2am Mon 23 Sep at the following locations to facilitate rail replacement bus operations for Metro North West Line trackwork:

  • Railway St, southbound between Day St & Help St,
  • Brown St, westbound between Railway St & Pacific Hwy.

A no-stopping zone will also be in place on Railway St, Chatswood, northbound between Help St and Brown St during this time.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, and apply even to local residents and businesses with parking permits or TfNSW Mobility Scheme permit holders. If your vehicle is towed, you can search your vehicle registration at the Find My Car website to find its new location, or alternatively call 132 701 to speak to an operator.
